WEBVTT

00:02:09.596 --> 00:02:14.734
Cowboy Bebop Season 1

00:02:16.669 --> 00:02:21.574
ASTEROID BLUES

00:03:06.953 --> 00:03:08.354
Hey, Spike.

00:03:10.490 --> 00:03:13.393
-It's ready.
-I'm just about done myself.

00:03:13.459 --> 00:03:14.360
What's cooking?

00:03:14.861 --> 00:03:16.663
Special beef with bell peppers.

00:03:25.572 --> 00:03:29.275
Asimov Solensan. This is our next target.

00:03:30.677 --> 00:03:31.678
Hey, Jet...

00:03:31.744 --> 00:03:35.515
He's high up in the syndicate
that deals all around the asteroids.

00:03:35.582 --> 00:03:37.550
About this beef with bell peppers...

00:03:37.617 --> 00:03:40.787
The guy's name is Asimov Solensan.
Weren't you listening to me?

00:03:40.853 --> 00:03:43.556
You don't call
a meatless beef with bell peppers

00:03:43.623 --> 00:03:46.793
"beef with bell peppers," do you?

00:03:47.994 --> 00:03:49.495
Yes, you do.

00:03:50.230 --> 00:03:53.733
-No, you don't.
-You do when you're broke.

00:03:53.800 --> 00:03:56.803
What happened to the million-woolong
bounty from that last guy?

00:03:56.869 --> 00:03:59.539
The repair bill
for the plane you wrecked...

00:04:00.306 --> 00:04:02.575
and the shop you trashed...

00:04:02.642 --> 00:04:05.245
and the medical bill
of the cop you injured

00:04:05.311 --> 00:04:06.012
killed the dough!

00:04:08.982 --> 00:04:13.686
Three days ago, there was a shootout
between his group and an enemy syndicate.

00:04:14.554 --> 00:04:16.956
He killed his own men and took off.

00:04:17.657 --> 00:04:20.860
They say he's hiding
with his woman in Tijuana.

00:04:20.927 --> 00:04:23.596
That's a place for nobodies to go.

00:04:23.663 --> 00:04:26.733
Despite being a nobody,
he's worth 2.5 million.

00:04:26.799 --> 00:04:28.501
Don't feel like it.

00:04:28.568 --> 00:04:32.705
Tijuana... The beef there is really tasty.

00:04:53.293 --> 00:04:57.397
<i>Attention, please.</i>
<i>We will soon arrive at the gate.</i>

00:04:58.531 --> 00:05:02.335
<i>We look forward to serving you again.</i>

00:05:15.615 --> 00:05:18.851
I'll head over
after hitting up the cops for clues.

00:05:18.918 --> 00:05:21.954
Then I'll try seeing old man Bull.

00:05:22.789 --> 00:05:24.924
<i>Can you trust that old guy?</i>

00:05:53.953 --> 00:05:55.855
Such an easygoing song.

00:06:18.111 --> 00:06:19.545
Thief!

00:06:29.689 --> 00:06:31.891
This again? Goddamn son of a bitch.

00:06:32.825 --> 00:06:35.862
Man, you're totally ripping me off,

00:06:35.928 --> 00:06:38.431
but do you realize
the reason you can live here

00:06:38.498 --> 00:06:42.401
is because I dug that gate
with all my might?

00:06:42.468 --> 00:06:45.404
This again.
You always say that when you lose.

00:06:45.471 --> 00:06:48.741
We all dug the gate together, remember?

00:06:48.808 --> 00:06:52.545
That we did.
We dug like there was no tomorrow.

00:06:52.612 --> 00:06:54.580
Goddamn idiot son of a bitch!

00:07:09.562 --> 00:07:10.663
Give me a beer.

00:07:10.730 --> 00:07:13.533
And I'll have a bloody mary.

00:07:16.803 --> 00:07:19.906
I got vodka, but unfortunately,
I'm out of tomato juice.

00:07:20.807 --> 00:07:23.109
I'm sure there's one can in the back room.

00:07:25.545 --> 00:07:26.546
I'll take a look.

00:07:37.757 --> 00:07:41.194
Top-notch Red-Eye.
You'd know, as a buyer, right?

00:07:41.461 --> 00:07:43.996
Can it be... Bloody-Eye?

00:07:53.039 --> 00:07:55.708
Prove to me that it's the real thing.

00:08:20.633 --> 00:08:22.702
Keep those eyes open.

00:09:28.034 --> 00:09:31.103
This is dandy,
but you got anything to eat?

00:09:35.875 --> 00:09:36.943
I see.

00:09:40.012 --> 00:09:44.717
The red-eyed coyote will appear
at the north end of town.

00:09:44.784 --> 00:09:46.018
That is what I see.

00:09:46.819 --> 00:09:48.754
A red-eyed coyote, huh?

00:09:48.821 --> 00:09:50.156
You, Swimming Bird...

00:09:51.657 --> 00:09:53.759
You shall meet a woman.

00:09:53.826 --> 00:09:56.128
You shall be targeted by that woman.

00:09:56.862 --> 00:09:59.031
And then death.

00:10:00.199 --> 00:10:02.702
-Again. I see.
-Again?

00:10:03.169 --> 00:10:04.870
I've already died once.

00:10:05.705 --> 00:10:06.872
Got killed by a woman.

00:10:07.306 --> 00:10:09.942
You take women too lightly.

00:10:10.676 --> 00:10:11.611
Catch you later.

00:10:14.680 --> 00:10:16.882
May he be blessed by Wakantanka.

00:10:28.761 --> 00:10:30.363
Presidente?

00:10:31.163 --> 00:10:32.798
I'll have a glass on the house.

00:10:38.971 --> 00:10:42.074
Damn. Asimov sure lost his head.

00:10:42.141 --> 00:10:45.978
No shit. We gotta do something
before the cops start moving.

00:10:46.045 --> 00:10:48.247
You wanna leave it up to the cops?

00:10:48.314 --> 00:10:50.249
He is using those eye drops.

00:10:50.916 --> 00:10:52.084
There's no way we can win.

00:10:52.151 --> 00:10:56.422
I'm telling you, we got nothing
if we don't get that Bloody-Eye back.

00:10:56.689 --> 00:10:57.690
But, man...

00:10:58.658 --> 00:10:59.358
Hey.

00:11:03.095 --> 00:11:04.964
Can you give me the specifics?

00:11:14.073 --> 00:11:15.408
Man, I'm hungry.

00:11:18.878 --> 00:11:19.979
You, too?

00:12:00.853 --> 00:12:02.922
It's better to leave the water running.

00:12:06.926 --> 00:12:07.860
Or it'll clog.

00:12:29.381 --> 00:12:30.483
Oh, I'm sorry.

00:12:35.221 --> 00:12:36.222
Thank you.

00:12:44.430 --> 00:12:45.331
I'm sorry.

00:12:46.799 --> 00:12:49.135
I don't want that anymore.
You can have it.

00:12:58.377 --> 00:13:01.480
I'm really sorry, honest.
Felt like my stomach was glued to my back.

00:13:08.320 --> 00:13:09.488
Nice fighter.

00:13:09.555 --> 00:13:12.558
It's an old model.
She's been with me for over ten years.

00:13:12.825 --> 00:13:15.327
Looks like you've gotten a lot
of use out of it.

00:13:15.394 --> 00:13:17.096
I travel around a lot.

00:13:18.230 --> 00:13:20.166
I'm actually a wandering performer.

00:13:22.902 --> 00:13:25.371
I can't tell if you're for real
or just joking.

00:13:25.437 --> 00:13:27.106
A lot of people say that about me.

00:13:27.907 --> 00:13:30.276
-Been to Mars yet?
-I was born on Mars.

00:13:31.243 --> 00:13:33.078
They have everything there.

00:13:33.846 --> 00:13:38.450
Unlike here, Mars has lots of people,
lots of things...

00:13:38.517 --> 00:13:40.085
They must live happily there.

00:13:41.420 --> 00:13:42.588
Only the rich.

00:13:43.989 --> 00:13:46.225
Then I'm sure we'll be happy there.

00:13:53.065 --> 00:13:58.137
You planning on escaping to Mars?
Running away... But how far can you go?

00:13:58.837 --> 00:13:59.505
Who are you?

00:14:00.306 --> 00:14:02.274
An old-fashioned cowboy.

00:14:03.309 --> 00:14:04.443
A bounty hunter?

00:14:05.211 --> 00:14:06.145
Good call.

00:14:07.213 --> 00:14:08.480
You're not going to catch us?

00:14:09.215 --> 00:14:11.317
Your buddy seems to be pretty ill.

00:14:12.017 --> 00:14:13.986
I don't deal with weakened nobodies.

00:14:15.321 --> 00:14:16.555
Wise decision.

00:14:19.425 --> 00:14:20.593
You are the nobody.

00:14:27.533 --> 00:14:29.101
Asimov. That's enough.

00:14:41.280 --> 00:14:42.514
Adios, cowboy.

00:14:56.362 --> 00:14:57.363
Why did you stop me?

00:14:59.031 --> 00:15:02.534
I could have killed him in a second.

00:15:02.601 --> 00:15:05.271
You're tired. If you do this anymore...

00:15:05.337 --> 00:15:07.106
He was young and attractive.

00:15:10.109 --> 00:15:14.213
I was waiting for so long
for you to come pick me up.

00:15:15.147 --> 00:15:17.483
I can finally escape
the lowly life I've had here.

00:15:19.518 --> 00:15:21.387
I can finally live happily on Mars.

00:15:34.533 --> 00:15:36.302
A nap. How peaceful.

00:15:37.002 --> 00:15:39.672
-I had a good dream.
-That's great.

00:15:40.272 --> 00:15:43.943
You can see the rest of that dream
on the <i>Bebop.</i>

00:15:44.009 --> 00:15:45.945
I'm giving up on this one.

00:15:46.011 --> 00:15:47.980
It's impossible to catch him.

00:15:48.480 --> 00:15:50.149
There's no way we can win.

00:15:50.482 --> 00:15:54.153
When Asimov left his syndicate,
he snuck something out with him.

00:15:54.653 --> 00:15:59.458
The top-end stuff of all the illegal
eye drops that the syndicate makes.

00:16:00.092 --> 00:16:04.330
He took off with all of the drops,
so, the group is in a mess.

00:16:04.396 --> 00:16:07.232
They wanna catch him,
but all they get back are corpses.

00:16:07.733 --> 00:16:09.735
Because Asimov is using it...

00:16:10.002 --> 00:16:13.138
The eye drops known as Bloody-Eye.

00:16:13.205 --> 00:16:15.474
They're planning on going to Mars.

00:16:15.541 --> 00:16:16.608
Mars?

00:16:16.675 --> 00:16:18.677
But before that, they'll sell this off.

00:16:20.245 --> 00:16:23.148
-That's...
-I grabbed it from his breast pocket.

00:16:23.215 --> 00:16:25.384
You... met him?

00:16:25.451 --> 00:16:27.086
A nightmare.

00:16:28.320 --> 00:16:29.521
He got you?

00:16:29.588 --> 00:16:33.425
The red-eyed coyote will supposedly appear
at the north end of town.

00:16:54.213 --> 00:16:57.016
This again? Goddamn son of a bitch.

00:16:57.716 --> 00:17:00.686
Man, you're totally ripping me off,

00:17:00.753 --> 00:17:04.356
but do you realize the reason
you can eat well around here

00:17:04.423 --> 00:17:07.326
is because I cultivated the land
with my buddies, you hear?

00:17:07.393 --> 00:17:09.328
Yeah, and that's us.

00:17:09.395 --> 00:17:11.263
That we did.

00:17:11.330 --> 00:17:13.732
We planted seeds
like there was no tomorrow.

00:17:13.799 --> 00:17:17.069
You were always planting seeds
of a different kind, though.

00:17:29.681 --> 00:17:31.383
Do you have bloody marys?

00:17:32.051 --> 00:17:33.185
I only got beer.

00:17:34.119 --> 00:17:35.354
I've got tomato juice.

00:17:36.055 --> 00:17:36.789
How much?

00:17:37.056 --> 00:17:38.690
Three hundred thousand woolongs.

00:17:38.757 --> 00:17:39.658
I got 50 packs.

00:17:40.259 --> 00:17:42.127
Fifteen million Woolongs, eh?

00:17:42.194 --> 00:17:44.730
I'm in a hurry.
I'll find others if you don't want it.

00:17:45.764 --> 00:17:46.632
Show me.

00:17:50.836 --> 00:17:52.237
Looking for this?

00:17:53.705 --> 00:17:55.841
Hey, do you know what you are worth?

00:17:56.675 --> 00:18:00.279
-What?
-Only 2.5 million woolongs.

00:18:00.712 --> 00:18:02.281
You're such a cheap guy.

00:18:05.384 --> 00:18:06.518
Long time, no see.

00:18:06.585 --> 00:18:09.688
Since when are you a buyer?
Did you give up on bounty hunting?

00:18:10.456 --> 00:18:13.092
No thrill in cheap bounties.

00:18:13.759 --> 00:18:15.694
Looks like you do better as a thief.

00:18:16.428 --> 00:18:17.463
Give it back.

00:18:18.230 --> 00:18:19.331
Sure, I will.

00:18:19.398 --> 00:18:20.632
I owe you one--

00:18:36.882 --> 00:18:38.650
You trust your eyes too much.

00:18:38.717 --> 00:18:41.687
You're not a chameleon.
You can't see everywhere at once.

00:19:04.143 --> 00:19:04.810
Let's go!

00:19:06.245 --> 00:19:07.312
That way!

00:19:09.681 --> 00:19:10.716
That way!

00:19:11.483 --> 00:19:12.618
What the hell are you--?!

00:19:13.852 --> 00:19:15.287
Don't move!

00:19:15.354 --> 00:19:17.623
All right, stay still.

00:19:27.432 --> 00:19:28.534
Idiot!

00:19:29.234 --> 00:19:31.803
We're doomed if these break.
Be more careful.

00:19:50.956 --> 00:19:52.391
Sorry to keep you waiting.

00:19:52.457 --> 00:19:54.193
You're late, Jet.

00:19:55.227 --> 00:19:56.228
Shit.

00:20:05.671 --> 00:20:06.605
Asimov.

00:20:33.498 --> 00:20:35.934
Stop! Doing any more is insane.
Don't do it.

00:20:36.969 --> 00:20:37.869
Don't!

00:20:57.956 --> 00:20:59.358
We can't run anymore.

00:21:00.792 --> 00:21:02.361
There's no way we can get away.

00:21:44.536 --> 00:21:46.605
Hey, Spike, it's ready.

00:22:12.698 --> 00:22:14.633
-It's ready.
-What's cooking?

00:22:15.667 --> 00:22:17.436
Special beef with bell peppers.

00:22:47.099 --> 00:22:52.137
<i>Too much time has passed by</i>

00:22:52.671 --> 00:22:57.042
<i>To lament that we were deeply in love</i>

00:22:59.044 --> 00:23:04.082
<i>The wind keeps blowing, while my heart</i>

00:23:05.117 --> 00:23:09.688
<i>Cannot heal all the tears in it</i>

00:23:11.656 --> 00:23:18.663
<i>Someone cry for me with parched eyes.</i>

00:23:22.100 --> 00:23:25.403
<i>The real folk blues</i>

00:23:25.837 --> 00:23:28.940
<i>I only want to know</i>

00:23:29.841 --> 00:23:33.912
<i>What true sadness is</i>

00:23:33.979 --> 00:23:36.915
<i>Sitting in muddy water</i>

00:23:37.816 --> 00:23:40.152
<i>Isn't such a bad life</i>

00:23:41.620 --> 00:23:48.627
<i>If it ends</i>

00:23:51.463 --> 00:23:54.666
<i>After the first time</i>

00:24:10.849 --> 00:24:11.950
COMING EPISODE

00:24:12.017 --> 00:24:14.986
<i>-This program is finally under way.</i>
<i>-What's the meaning of this?</i>

00:24:15.053 --> 00:24:18.657
<i>Next week we're completely changing gears</i>
<i>to show an anime for all ages.</i>

00:24:18.723 --> 00:24:20.625
<i>Cheerful animals wreak havoc all over.</i>

00:24:20.692 --> 00:24:22.828
<i>-What?</i>
<i>-But an animal expert isn't coming.</i>

00:24:22.894 --> 00:24:24.963
<i>From little kids to the elderly,</i>
<i>if you love animals...</i>

00:24:25.030 --> 00:24:26.898
<i>Hold on, Spike.</i>

00:24:26.965 --> 00:24:31.603
<i>-Everyone gather round and watch the show.</i>
<i>-Is it okay to say stuff like that?</i>

00:24:31.670 --> 00:24:32.771
<i>But I ask one favor.</i>

00:24:33.471 --> 00:24:36.942
<i>Good kids should sit far from the TV.</i>
<i>Stand back about a kilometer.</i>

00:24:37.008 --> 00:24:37.876
STRAY DOG STRUT

00:24:37.943 --> 00:24:39.911
<i>-Too far.</i>
<i>-Eight hundred meters, then?</i>

